<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-04-15T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-04-15T12:00:00-05:00" n="541" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d541">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">693.006/38: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-04-15T12:00:00-05:00">April 15,
                                1938—noon.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>125. Your 199, April 11, 2 p.m., in regard to possible curtailment by
                            China of unessential imports.</p>
                        <p>You may orally and confidentially inform Young that the Department is
                            confident that, in connection with any measures which China may take for
                            the protection of her national economy, the Chinese Government would
                            give due consideration to American interests and would avoid any
                            discrimination against those interests.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
